  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nWhen trying to create a new group chat with many members, \r\nthe modal displays a weird behaviour after selecting a few members from the list.\r\nAfter selecting a couple of members from the top in the list members scroll down and scroll back up. \r\nThis selected list changes, however, the correct no.of selected contacts is displayed at the top of the modal.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n1 - Add contacts\r\n2 - Go to Chat and hit 'Start a new Group chat'\r\n3 - Select a few contacts to add in the group \r\n4 - Scroll down the list, and scroll back up\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior:\r\nThe selected list must remain selected\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nhttps://www.loom.com/share/6843b56d46e54c85922c0049bb6cf335\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: Master - commit: ba0e0b84c08f061748b2be11d0a6156779d87fc7\r\n\r\n",
